        <abstract> 
<p>Read GA’s book [<hi rend="italic">The colour-sense</hi>] with "<hi rend="italic">great interest</hi>". Makes criticisms and suggestions.</p> 
            <p>Cannot believe in GA’s theory of the origin of pleasure and pain.</p>
            <p>Is glad he defends sexual selection;</p>
            <p>CD finds A. R. Wallace’s explanations "mere empty words" and for many years he has "quite doubted [ARW’s] scientific judgment".</p>
            <p>Considers the possible effect of environmental colour on the colour tastes of animals.</p>
        </abstract>
